parameters:
Zerachiel: W-Wait! You've got the wrong
person, okay!?

Noble: I-I see... I apologize for
that...

Noble: You resembled my deceased wife
too much...

Zerachiel: I'm Zerachiel, I'm a
different person from your wife.

Noble: I see, Zerachiel... You're like a
spitting image of my wife...

Noble: Excuse me for asking something
rude, but would you spend the night with
me?

Zerachiel: Huh? That's sudden. If you're
not careful, you might get caught by the
knights.

Noble: If you, who looks just like my
wife, could relieve my loneliness,
maybe...

Noble: Of course, I'll pay if it's
money. How about 1000 Rill?

Zerachiel: (That's a huge amount of
money, what should I do...)

Noble: I was satisfied last night, thank
you. This is the promised money.

Zerachiel: Thank you so much... for this
many...!!

Noble: If you feel like it, come and
visit again. I'll welcome you.

Zerachiel: Understood, please take care
of me then.

Noble: The angels who attacked were
identical to my wife.

Noble: ...I remembered the words my wife
used to say a long time ago.
Noble: I'm not the real one.

Noble: My wife must have had some
connection with them. And so do you.

Noble: There's no need to make such a
sad face. You are you.
Noble: Please value your own will.

Noble: You are different from the other
angels. Because you are alive.
Noble: It's you, I'm glad you're safe.
Noble: Are you staying over tonight?

Noble: Hey, welcome. How about spending
tonight together again?

This is an event that has already
occurred. Would you like to skip it?

Noble: You can come and play anytime.
I'll welcome you, because it's you.

Noble: You can come and play anytime.
I'll welcome you, because it's you.

Noble: Come and play anytime. I'll
welcome you, because it's you.

Noble: It's you, thank goodness you're
safe.

Noble: Are you staying overnight
tonight?

Noble: Hey, welcome. How about staying
together tonight too?

This is an event that has already
occurred. Would you like to skip it?

Noble: Come and visit anytime. I'll
welcome you.

Noble: Come and visit anytime. I'll
welcome you.

Noble: Come and visit anytime. I'll
welcome you.
Noble: Are you going on a journey soon?

Noble: ...It's fine if it's just
occasionally. When you remember, please
come back to the mansion.

Zerachiel: (What should I do at the
end...)

This is an event that has already
occurred. Would you like to skip it?

Noble: Thank you. I'm praying for your
happiness.

Noble: Thank you. I'm praying for your
happiness.

Noble: Thank you. I'm praying for your
good fortune.

Noble: It reminds me of my late wife.
You really look just like her...
Zerachiel: No, I'm not your mom.

Girl: Your face, voice, and height are
all so similar... I mistook you for
someone else...

Girl: Since Mom passed away, Dad hasn't
been feeling well...

Girl: I wish Dad could go back to how he
used to be.

Girl: Papa, I've been feeling brighter
lately. Is it thanks to Onee-chan?

Girl: The maids, why are they so
infatuated with Papa?

Girl: Onee-chan, you're going on a
journey, right? Promise me you'll come
back to see me!

Girl: Mama taught me the pleasure of
being naked, but Onee-chan, does it feel
good for you too?

Zerachiel: I wonder why there's a scythe
here...

Maid: Master, after losing your wife,
you became like an empty shell filled
with sadness...

Maid: So you spent the night with your
master. Somehow, I had a feeling it
would turn out like this.
Maid: You somehow resemble the mistress.

Maid: Master, you saved us at the risk
of your life. I have reevaluated you.

Maid: Won't you become a maid? Your
master will be pleased too.

Maid: Madam, always playing pranks...
Occasionally, she would get caught by
the knights.
